# Path to the OneDrive "NEW - JIRAH MASTER" folder (the JIRAH workspace root).
# The reader descends into `01 - Clients/Active/`, `02 - Sales & Pipeline/Prospects/`,
# and `02 - Sales & Pipeline/Audit Applications/` from this root.
#
# IMPORTANT — this path differs per machine:
#   OneDrive for Business prefixes *shared* folders with the owner's name on the
#   RECEIVING side. The share owner's own machine does NOT see the prefix.
#   Each partner's Windows username also differs. Do not hardcode either variant.
#
# Jason's machine (receiving Joshua's share):
#   ONEDRIVE_ROOT="C:\\Users\\jason\\OneDrive - jirahgrowth.consulting\\Joshua Marshall's files - JIRAH Growth Partners - Shared\\NEW - JIRAH MASTER"
#
# Joshua's machine (share owner, no owner-prefix):
#   ONEDRIVE_ROOT="C:\\Users\\joshu\\OneDrive - jirahgrowth.consulting\\JIRAH Growth Partners - Shared\\NEW - JIRAH MASTER"
#
# Copy ONE of the two lines above, remove the leading `# `, adjust the Windows
# username if yours differs, save as `dashboard/.env.local` (gitignored).
